        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/96bed5/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2022-01-05T23:03:10.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi all</p>\n<p>I have been doing some research on Les Cailleret (the Puligny-Montrachet one) and am a bit confused by Clos Du Cailleret which I can\u2019t seem to see on any maps. I am correct in saying that it sits inside Les Cailleret?</p>\n<p>It seems as though Dom. Jean Chartron had it as a Monopole until the 2017 vintage based on their bottle labels yet Dom. des Lambrays has produced a Clos Du Cailleret for a number of years (seemingly going back to at least 1995 based on CT). So how is it possible that Chartron labelled bottles as Monopole when Lambray was producing one as well?</p>\n<p>Thank you!</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-04T11:10:35.019Z",
        "reply_count": 1,
        "reply_to_post_number": null,
